commit.message:
feat(plugins): use librime's internal plugin loader

BREAKING CHANGE: Configuration for plugins and modules to load in
ibus_rime.yaml is deprecated. (added after ibus-rime 1.4 release)

Instead, librime>=1.7 scans RIME plugin libraries installed at the
configured path RIME_PLUGINS_DIR which defaults to
/usr/lib/rime-plugins. Unlike the old behaviour, a RIME plugin library
loaded by librime is not unloaded on deploy. So updates to RIME plugin
libraries take effect until `ibus restart`.

refactor: update cmake script and rime_config.h.in

deprecate old user data dir ~/.config/rime/

Delete install.sh

the script was used for convenience.
please follow the `make && make install` convention.

commit.message:
feat(plugin): dynamically load librime plugins read from `ibus_rime.yaml` (#73)

* feat(plugin): dynamically load librime plugins read from `ibus_rime.yaml`

* fix(logging): add missing setup()

* fix(plugin): don't free any until the process is about to terminate

* refactor: use config_list_size()

* refactor & fix

- rename/split load_plugins() -> load_plugins_modules(), load_plugins(), load_modules()
- fix the issue that the module list is skipped when `n == 0 && n_plugins == 0`
- add missing `config_close()` call
- check return value of `dlopen()`

* fix: fix the merged plugins issue.
chore(rime.xml, rime_main.c): update ibus component name

chore(submodules): update librime, plum

Note: upate librime because it needs a higher version of 'boost',
an indirect dependency to ibus-rime. ibus-rime still works with
older librime before that update, so the minimum required version
of librime has not changed.
fix(CMakeLists.txt): static build requires boost_locale and icuuc
